71 // Include standard C++ headers.

84 // Detect/configure OS variables.
85 //
86 // Define 'cimg_OS' to: '0' for an unknown OS (will try to minize library dependencies).
87 // '1' for a Unix-like OS (Linux, Solaris, BSD, MacOSX, Irix, ...).
88 // '2' for Microsoft Windows.
89 // (auto-detection is performed if 'cimg_OS' is not set by the user).
90 #ifndef cimg_OS
91 #if defined(unix) || defined(__unix) || defined(__unix__) \
92  || defined(linux) || defined(__linux) || defined(__linux__) \
93  || defined(sun) || defined(__sun) \
94  || defined(BSD) || defined(__OpenBSD__) || defined(__NetBSD__) \
95  || defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined (__DragonFly__) \
96  || defined(sgi) || defined(__sgi) \
97  || defined(__MACOSX__) || defined(__APPLE__) \
98  || defined(__CYGWIN__)
99 #define cimg_OS 1
100 #elif defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(WIN32) || defined(_WIN32) || defined(__WIN32__) \
101  || defined(WIN64) || defined(_WIN64) || defined(__WIN64__)
102 #define cimg_OS 2
103 #else
104 #define cimg_OS 0
105 #endif
106 #elif !(cimg_OS==0 || cimg_OS==1 || cimg_OS==2)
107 #error CImg Library: Invalid configuration variable 'cimg_OS'.
108 #error (correct values are '0 = unknown OS', '1 = Unix-like OS', '2 = Microsoft Windows').
109 #endif
110 #ifndef cimg_date
111 #define cimg_date __DATE__
112 #endif
113 #ifndef cimg_time
114 #define cimg_time __TIME__
115 #endif
116

122 #pragma warning(disable:4311)
123 #pragma warning(disable:4312)
124 #pragma warning(disable:4319)
125 #pragma warning(disable:4512)
126 #pragma warning(disable:4571)
127 #pragma warning(disable:4640)
128 #pragma warning(disable:4706)
129 #pragma warning(disable:4710)
130 #pragma warning(disable:4800)
131 #pragma warning(disable:4804)
132 #pragma warning(disable:4820)
133 #pragma warning(disable:4996)
134 #define _CRT_SECURE_NO_DEPRECATE 1
135 #define _CRT_SECURE_NO_WARNINGS 1
136 #define _CRT_NONSTDC_NO_DEPRECATE 1
137 #endif

209 #if cimg_OS==2
210

213 #define cimg_ulong UINT_PTR
214 #define cimg_long INT_PTR

216 #define cimg_fuint64 "%I64u"
217 #define cimg_fint64 "%I64d"
218 #else
219 #define cimg_fuint64 "%llu"
220 #define cimg_fint64 "%lld"
221 #endif
222 
223 #else
224 
225 #if UINTPTR_MAX==0xffffffff || defined(__arm__) || defined(_M_ARM)
226 #define cimg_uint64 unsigned long long
227 #define cimg_int64 long long
228 #define cimg_fuint64 "%llu"
229 #define cimg_fint64 "%lld"
230 #else
231 #define cimg_uint64 unsigned long
232 #define cimg_int64 long
233 #define cimg_fuint64 "%lu"
234 #define cimg_fint64 "%ld"
235 #endif
236 
237 #if defined(__arm__) || defined(_M_ARM)
238 #define cimg_ulong unsigned long long
239 #define cimg_long long long
240 #else
241 #define cimg_ulong unsigned long
242 #define cimg_long long
243 #endif
244 
245 #endif

258 // Configure verbosity of output messages.
259 //
260 // Define 'cimg_verbosity' to: '0' to hide library messages (quiet mode).
261 // '1' to output library messages on the console.
262 // '2' to output library messages on a basic dialog window (default behavior).
263 // '3' to do as '1' + add extra warnings (may slow down the code!).
264 // '4' to do as '2' + add extra warnings (may slow down the code!).
265 //
266 // Define 'cimg_strict_warnings' to replace warning messages by exception throwns.
267 //
268 // Define 'cimg_use_vt100' to allow output of color messages on VT100-compatible terminals.
269 #ifndef cimg_verbosity
270 #if cimg_OS==2
271 #define cimg_verbosity 2
272 #else
273 #define cimg_verbosity 1
274 #endif
275 #elif !(cimg_verbosity==0 || cimg_verbosity==1 || cimg_verbosity==2 || cimg_verbosity==3 || cimg_verbosity==4)
276 #error CImg Library: Configuration variable 'cimg_verbosity' is badly defined.
277 #error (should be { 0=quiet | 1=console | 2=dialog | 3=console+warnings | 4=dialog+warnings }).
278 #endif

280 // Configure display framework.
281 //
282 // Define 'cimg_display' to: '0' to disable display capabilities.
283 // '1' to use the X-Window framework (X11).
284 // '2' to use the Microsoft GDI32 framework.
285 #ifndef cimg_display
286 #if cimg_OS==0
287 #define cimg_display 0
288 #elif cimg_OS==1
289 #define cimg_display 1
290 #elif cimg_OS==2
291 #define cimg_display 2
292 #endif
293 #elif !(cimg_display==0 || cimg_display==1 || cimg_display==2)
294 #error CImg Library: Configuration variable 'cimg_display' is badly defined.
295 #error (should be { 0=none | 1=X-Window (X11) | 2=Microsoft GDI32 }).
296 #endif

298 // Configure the 'abort' signal handler (does nothing by default).
299 // A typical signal handler can be defined in your own source like this:
300 // #define cimg_abort_test() if (is_abort) throw CImgAbortException("")
301 //
302 // where 'is_abort' is a boolean variable defined somewhere in your code and reachable in the method.
303 // 'cimg_abort_test2()' does the same but is called more often (in inner loops).
304 #if defined(cimg_abort_test) && defined(cimg_use_openmp)
305 
306 // Define abort macros to be used with OpenMP.
307 #ifndef cimg_abort_init
308 #define cimg_abort_init bool cimg_abort_go = true; cimg::unused(cimg_abort_go)
309 #endif
310 #ifndef cimg_abort_try
311 #define cimg_abort_try if (cimg_abort_go) try
312 #endif
313 #ifndef cimg_abort_catch
314 #define cimg_abort_catch() catch (CImgAbortException&) { cimg_pragma(omp atomic) cimg_abort_go&=false; }
315 #endif
316 #ifdef cimg_abort_test2
317 #ifndef cimg_abort_try2
318 #define cimg_abort_try2 cimg_abort_try
319 #endif
320 #ifndef cimg_abort_catch2
321 #define cimg_abort_catch2() cimg_abort_catch()
322 #endif
323 #ifndef cimg_abort_catch_fill
324 #define cimg_abort_catch_fill() \
325  catch (CImgException& e) { cimg_pragma(omp critical) CImg<charT>::string(e._message).move_to(is_error); \
326  cimg_pragma(omp atomic) cimg_abort_go&=false; }
327 #endif
328 #endif
329 
330 #endif
331 
332 #ifndef cimg_abort_test
333 #define cimg_abort_test()
334 #endif
335 #ifndef cimg_abort_test2
336 #define cimg_abort_test2()
337 #endif
338 #ifndef cimg_abort_init
339 #define cimg_abort_init
340 #endif
341 #ifndef cimg_abort_try
342 #define cimg_abort_try
343 #endif
344 #ifndef cimg_abort_catch
345 #define cimg_abort_catch()
346 #endif
347 #ifndef cimg_abort_try2
348 #define cimg_abort_try2
349 #endif
350 #ifndef cimg_abort_catch2
351 #define cimg_abort_catch2()
352 #endif
353 #ifndef cimg_abort_catch_fill
354 #define cimg_abort_catch_fill()
355 #endif
356 #ifndef std_fopen
357 #define std_fopen std::fopen
358 #endif

379 // Configure OpenMP support.

382 // Define 'cimg_use_openmp' to enable OpenMP support.

384 // OpenMP directives may be used in a (very) few CImg functions to get
385 // advantages of multi-core CPUs.

573  extern void ssyev_(char*, char*, int*, float*, int*, float*, float*, int*, int*);

576  extern void dgetrs_(char*, int*, int*, double*, int*, int*, double*, int*, int*);
577  extern void dgesvd_(char*, char*, int*, int*, double*, int*, double*, double*,
578  int*, double*, int*, double*, int*, int*);
579  extern void dsyev_(char*, char*, int*, double*, int*, double*, double*, int*, int*);
580  extern void dgels_(char*, int*,int*,int*,double*,int*,double*,int*,double*,int*,int*);
581  extern void sgels_(char*, int*,int*,int*,float*,int*,float*,int*,float*,int*,int*);
582 }
583 #endif

585 // Check if min/max/PI macros are defined.
586 //
587 // CImg does not compile if macros 'min', 'max' or 'PI' are defined,
588 // because it redefines functions min(), max() and const variable PI in the cimg:: namespace.
589 // so it '#undef' these macros if necessary, and restore them to reasonable
590 // values at the end of this file.
591 #ifdef min
592 #undef min
593 #define _cimg_redefine_min
594 #endif
595 #ifdef max
596 #undef max
597 #define _cimg_redefine_max
598 #endif
599 #ifdef PI
600 #undef PI
601 #define _cimg_redefine_PI
602 #endif
603 
604 // Define 'cimg_library' namespace suffix.
605 //
606 // You may want to add a suffix to the 'cimg_library' namespace, for instance if you need to work
607 // with several versions of the library at the same time.
608 #ifdef cimg_namespace_suffix
609 #define __cimg_library_suffixed(s) cimg_library_##s
610 #define _cimg_library_suffixed(s) __cimg_library_suffixed(s)
611 #define cimg_library_suffixed _cimg_library_suffixed(cimg_namespace_suffix)
612 #else
613 #define cimg_library_suffixed cimg_library
614 #endif

616 /*------------------------------------------------------------------------------
617  #
618  # Define user-friendly macros.
619  #
620  # These CImg macros are prefixed by 'cimg_' and can be used safely in your own
621  # code. They are useful to parse command line options, or to write image loops.
622  #
623  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
624 
625 // Macros to define program usage, and retrieve command line arguments.
626 #define cimg_usage(usage) cimg_library_suffixed::cimg::option((char*)0,argc,argv,(char*)0,usage,false)
627 #define cimg_help(str) cimg_library_suffixed::cimg::option((char*)0,argc,argv,str,(char*)0)
628 #define cimg_option(name,defaut,usage) cimg_library_suffixed::cimg::option(name,argc,argv,defaut,usage)

630 // Macros to define and manipulate local neighborhoods.
631 #define CImg_2x2(I,T) T I[4]; \
632  T& I##cc = I[0]; T& I##nc = I[1]; \
633  T& I##cn = I[2]; T& I##nn = I[3]; \
634  I##cc = I##nc = \
635  I##cn = I##nn = 0
636 
637 #define CImg_3x3(I,T) T I[9]; \
638  T& I##pp = I[0]; T& I##cp = I[1]; T& I##np = I[2]; \
639  T& I##pc = I[3]; T& I##cc = I[4]; T& I##nc = I[5]; \
640  T& I##pn = I[6]; T& I##cn = I[7]; T& I##nn = I[8]; \
641  I##pp = I##cp = I##np = \
642  I##pc = I##cc = I##nc = \
643  I##pn = I##cn = I##nn = 0
644

651  I##pc = I##cc = I##nc = I##ac = \
652  I##pn = I##cn = I##nn = I##an = \
653  I##pa = I##ca = I##na = I##aa = 0

954  _dy=(y1)>(y0)?(int)(y1) - (int)(y0):(_sy=-1,(int)(y0) - (int)(y1)), \
955  _counter = _dx, \
956  _err = _dx>_dy?(_dy>>1):((_steep=1),(_counter=_dy),(_dx>>1)); \
957  _counter>=0; \
958  --_counter, x+=_steep? \
959  (y+=_sy,(_err-=_dx)<0?_err+=_dy,_sx:0): \
960  (y+=(_err-=_dy)<0?_err+=_dx,_sy:0,_sx))

2261  // Mandatory because Microsoft's _snprintf() and _vsnprintf() do not add the '\0' character
2262  // at the end of the string.
2263 #if cimg_OS==2 && defined(_MSC_VER)
2264  inline int _snprintf(char *const s, const size_t size, const char *const format, ...) {
2265  va_list ap;
2266  va_start(ap,format);
2267  const int result = _vsnprintf(s,size,format,ap);
2268  va_end(ap);
2269  return result;
2270  }
2271 
2272  inline int _vsnprintf(char *const s, const size_t size, const char *const format, va_list ap) {
2273  int result = -1;
2274  cimg::mutex(6);
2275  if (size) result = _vsnprintf_s(s,size,_TRUNCATE,format,ap);
2276  if (result==-1) result = _vscprintf(format,ap);
2277  cimg::mutex(6,0);
2278  return result;
2279  }

2451  struct CImgException : public std::exception {
2452 #define _cimg_exception_err(etype,disp_flag) \
2453  std::va_list ap, ap2; \
2454  va_start(ap,format); va_start(ap2,format); \
2455  int size = cimg_vsnprintf(0,0,format,ap2); \
2456  if (size++>=0) { \
2457  delete[] _message; \
2458  _message = new char[size]; \
2459  cimg_vsnprintf(_message,size,format,ap); \
2460  if (cimg::exception_mode()) { \
2461  std::fprintf(cimg::output(),"\n%s[CImg] *** %s ***%s %s\n",cimg::t_red,etype,cimg::t_normal,_message); \
2462  if (cimg_display && disp_flag && !(cimg::exception_mode()%2)) try { cimg::dialog(etype,_message,"Abort"); } \
2463  catch (CImgException&) {} \
2464  if (cimg::exception_mode()>=3) cimg_library_suffixed::cimg::info(); \
2465  } \
2466  } \
2467  va_end(ap); va_end(ap2); \
2468 
2469  char *_message;
2470  CImgException() { _message = new char[1]; *_message = 0; }
2471  CImgException(const char *const format, ...):_message(0) { _cimg_exception_err("CImgException",true); }
2472  CImgException(const CImgException& e):std::exception(e) {
2473  const size_t size = std::strlen(e._message);
2474  _message = new char[size + 1];
2475  std::strncpy(_message,e._message,size);
2476  _message[size] = 0;
2477  }
2478  ~CImgException() throw() { delete[] _message; }
2479  CImgException& operator=(const CImgException& e) {
2480  const size_t size = std::strlen(e._message);
2481  _message = new char[size + 1];
2482  std::strncpy(_message,e._message,size);
2483  _message[size] = 0;
2484  return *this;
2485  }
2487  const char *what() const throw() { return _message; }
2488  };

2490  // The CImgAbortException class is used to throw an exception when
2491  // a computationally-intensive function has been aborted by an external signal.
2492  struct CImgAbortException : public std::exception {
2493  char *_message;
2494  CImgAbortException() { _message = new char[1]; *_message = 0; }
2495  CImgAbortException(const char *const format, ...):_message(0) { _cimg_exception_err("CImgAbortException",true); }
2496  CImgAbortException(const CImgAbortException& e):std::exception(e) {
2497  const size_t size = std::strlen(e._message);
2498  _message = new char[size + 1];
2499  std::strncpy(_message,e._message,size);
2500  _message[size] = 0;
2501  }
2502  ~CImgAbortException() throw() { delete[] _message; }
2503  CImgAbortException& operator=(const CImgAbortException& e) {
2504  const size_t size = std::strlen(e._message);
2505  _message = new char[size + 1];
2506  std::strncpy(_message,e._message,size);
2507  _message[size] = 0;
2508  return *this;
2509  }
2511  const char *what() const throw() { return _message; }
2512  };

2559  // Define traits that will be used to determine the best data type to work in CImg functions.
2560  //
2561  template<typename T> struct type {
2562  static const char* string() {
2563  static const char* s[] = { "unknown", "unknown8", "unknown16", "unknown24",
2564  "unknown32", "unknown40", "unknown48", "unknown56",
2565  "unknown64", "unknown72", "unknown80", "unknown88",
2566  "unknown96", "unknown104", "unknown112", "unknown120",
2567  "unknown128" };
2568  return s[(sizeof(T)<17)?sizeof(T):0];
2569  }
2570  static bool is_float() { return false; }
2571  static bool is_inf(const T) { return false; }
2572  static bool is_nan(const T) { return false; }
2573  static T min() { return ~max(); }
2574  static T max() { return (T)1<<(8*sizeof(T) - 1); }
2575  static T inf() { return max(); }
2576  static T cut(const double val) { return val<(double)min()?min():val>(double)max()?max():(T)val; }
2577  static const char* format() { return "%s"; }
2578  static const char* format_s() { return "%s"; }
2579  static const char* format(const T& val) { static const char *const s = "unknown"; cimg::unused(val); return s; }
2580  };

2583  static const char* string() { static const char *const s = "bool"; return s; }
2584  static bool is_float() { return false; }
2585  static bool is_inf(const bool) { return false; }
2586  static bool is_nan(const bool) { return false; }
2587  static bool min() { return false; }
2588  static bool max() { return true; }
2589  static bool inf() { return max(); }
2590  static bool is_inf() { return false; }
2591  static bool cut(const double val) { return val<(double)min()?min():val>(double)max()?max():(bool)val; }
2592  static const char* format() { return "%s"; }
2593  static const char* format_s() { return "%s"; }
2594  static const char* format(const bool val) { static const char* s[] = { "false", "true" }; return s[val?1:0]; }

2747  template<> struct type<double> {
2748  static const char* string() { static const char *const s = "double"; return s; }
2749  static bool is_float() { return true; }
2750  static bool is_inf(const double val) {
2751 #ifdef isinf
2752  return (bool)isinf(val);
2753 #else
2754  return !is_nan(val) && (val<cimg::type<double>::min() || val>cimg::type<double>::max());
2755 #endif
2756  }
2757  static bool is_nan(const double val) {
2758 #ifdef isnan
2759  return (bool)isnan(val);
2760 #else
2761  return !(val==val);
2762 #endif
2763  }
2764  static double min() { return -DBL_MAX; }
2765  static double max() { return DBL_MAX; }
2766  static double inf() {
2767 #ifdef INFINITY
2768  return (double)INFINITY;
2769 #else
2770  return max()*max();
2771 #endif
2772  }
2773  static double nan() {
2774 #ifdef NAN
2775  return (double)NAN;
2776 #else
2777  const double val_nan = -std::sqrt(-1.0); return val_nan;
2778 #endif
2779  }
2780  static double cut(const double val) { return val; }
2781  static const char* format() { return "%.17g"; }
2782  static const char* format_s() { return "%g"; }
2783  static double format(const double val) { return val; }
2784  };
2785

2790 #ifdef isinf
2791  return (bool)isinf(val);
2792 #else
2793  return !is_nan(val) && (val<cimg::type<float>::min() || val>cimg::type<float>::max());
2794 #endif
2795  }
2796  static bool is_nan(const float val) {
2797 #ifdef isnan
2798  return (bool)isnan(val);
2799 #else
2800  return !(val==val);
2801 #endif
2802  }
2803  static float min() { return -FLT_MAX; }
2804  static float max() { return FLT_MAX; }
2805  static float inf() { return (float)cimg::type<double>::inf(); }
2806  static float nan() { return (float)cimg::type<double>::nan(); }
2807  static float cut(const double val) { return (float)val; }
2808  static float cut(const float val) { return (float)val; }

2870  template<typename T, typename t> struct superset { typedef T type; };
2871  template<> struct superset<bool,unsigned char> { typedef unsigned char type; };

2958  template<> struct superset<half,float> { typedef float type; };
2959  template<> struct superset<half,double> { typedef double type; };
2960 #endif

2964  };

2968  };

2970  template<typename t1, typename t2> struct last { typedef t2 type; };

3049  struct Mutex_info {

3051  HANDLE mutex[32];
3052  Mutex_info() { for (unsigned int i = 0; i<32; ++i) mutex[i] = CreateMutex(0,FALSE,0); }
3053  void lock(const unsigned int n) { WaitForSingleObject(mutex[n],INFINITE); }
3054  void unlock(const unsigned int n) { ReleaseMutex(mutex[n]); }
3055  int trylock(const unsigned int) { return 0; }
3056 #elif defined(_PTHREAD_H)
3057  pthread_mutex_t mutex[32];
3058  Mutex_info() { for (unsigned int i = 0; i<32; ++i) pthread_mutex_init(&mutex[i],0); }
3059  void lock(const unsigned int n) { pthread_mutex_lock(&mutex[n]); }
3060  void unlock(const unsigned int n) { pthread_mutex_unlock(&mutex[n]); }
3061  int trylock(const unsigned int n) { return pthread_mutex_trylock(&mutex[n]); }
3062 #else
3063  Mutex_info() {}
3064  void lock(const unsigned int) {}
3065  void unlock(const unsigned int) {}
3066  int trylock(const unsigned int) { return 0; }
3067 #endif
3068  };

4793  // Lock/unlock mutex for CImg multi-thread programming.
4794  inline int mutex(const unsigned int n, const int lock_mode) {

4796  case 0 : cimg::Mutex_attr().unlock(n); return 0;
4797  case 1 : cimg::Mutex_attr().lock(n); return 0;
4798  default : return cimg::Mutex_attr().trylock(n);

4817  inline void warn(const char *const format, ...) {
4818  if (cimg::exception_mode()>=1) {
4819  char *const message = new char[16384];
4820  std::va_list ap;
4821  va_start(ap,format);
4822  cimg_vsnprintf(message,16384,format,ap);
4823  va_end(ap);
4824 #ifdef cimg_strict_warnings
4825  throw CImgWarningException(message);
4826 #else
4827  std::fprintf(cimg::output(),"\n%s[CImg] *** Warning ***%s%s\n",cimg::t_red,cimg::t_normal,message);
4828 #endif

4833  // Execute an external system command.
4842  inline int system(const char *const command, const char *const module_name=0) {
4843  cimg::unused(module_name);
4844 #ifdef cimg_no_system_calls
4845  return -1;
4846 #else
4847 #if cimg_OS==1
4848  const unsigned int l = (unsigned int)std::strlen(command);
4849  if (l) {
4850  char *const ncommand = new char[l + 16];
4851  std::strncpy(ncommand,command,l);
4852  std::strcpy(ncommand + l," 2> /dev/null"); // Make command silent.
4853  const int out_val = std::system(ncommand);
4854  delete[] ncommand;
4855  return out_val;
4856  } else return -1;
4857 #elif cimg_OS==2
4858  PROCESS_INFORMATION pi;
4859  STARTUPINFO si;
4860  std::memset(&pi,0,sizeof(PROCESS_INFORMATION));
4861  std::memset(&si,0,sizeof(STARTUPINFO));
4862  GetStartupInfo(&si);
4863  si.cb = sizeof(si);
4864  si.wShowWindow = SW_HIDE;
4865  si.dwFlags |= SW_HIDE | STARTF_USESHOWWINDOW;
4866  const BOOL res = CreateProcess((LPCTSTR)module_name,(LPTSTR)command,0,0,FALSE,0,0,0,&si,&pi);
4867  if (res) {
4868  WaitForSingleObject(pi.hProcess,INFINITE);
4869  CloseHandle(pi.hThread);
4870  CloseHandle(pi.hProcess);
4871  return 0;
4872  } else return std::system(command);
4873 #else
4874  return std::system(command);
4875 #endif
4876 #endif
4877  }

4948  template<typename T>
4949  inline void invert_endianness(T* const buffer, const cimg_ulong size) {
4950  if (size) switch (sizeof(T)) {
4951  case 1 : break;
4952  case 2 : { for (unsigned short *ptr = (unsigned short*)buffer + size; ptr>(unsigned short*)buffer; ) {
4953  const unsigned short val = *(--ptr);
4954  *ptr = (unsigned short)((val>>8)|((val<<8)));
4955  }
4956  } break;
4957  case 4 : { for (unsigned int *ptr = (unsigned int*)buffer + size; ptr>(unsigned int*)buffer; ) {
4958  const unsigned int val = *(--ptr);
4959  *ptr = (val>>24)|((val>>8)&0xff00)|((val<<8)&0xff0000)|(val<<24);
4960  }
4961  } break;
4962  default : { for (T* ptr = buffer + size; ptr>buffer; ) {
4963  unsigned char *pb = (unsigned char*)(--ptr), *pe = pb + sizeof(T);
4964  for (int i = 0; i<(int)sizeof(T)/2; ++i) swap(*(pb++),*(--pe));
4965  }
4966  }
4967  }
4968  }

4978  return a;
4979  }

4981  // Conversion functions to get more precision when trying to store unsigned ints values as floats.
4982  inline unsigned int float2uint(const float f) {
4983  int tmp = 0;
4984  std::memcpy(&tmp,&f,sizeof(float));
4985  if (tmp>=0) return (unsigned int)f;
4986  unsigned int u;
4987  // use memcpy instead of assignment to avoid undesired optimizations by C++-compiler.
4988  std::memcpy(&u,&f,sizeof(float));
4989  return ((u)<<1)>>1; // set sign bit to 0.
4990  }
4991 
4992  inline float uint2float(const unsigned int u) {
4993  if (u<(1U<<19)) return (float)u; // Consider safe storage of unsigned int as floats until 19bits (i.e 524287).
4994  float f;
4995  const unsigned int v = u|(1U<<(8*sizeof(unsigned int)-1)); // set sign bit to 1.
4996  // use memcpy instead of simple assignment to avoid undesired optimizations by C++-compiler.
4997  std::memcpy(&f,&v,sizeof(float));
4998  return f;
4999  }

5057  inline unsigned int _wait(const unsigned int milliseconds, cimg_ulong& timer) {
5058  if (!timer) timer = cimg::time();
5059  const cimg_ulong current_time = cimg::time();
5060  if (current_time>=timer + milliseconds) { timer = current_time; return 0; }
5061  const unsigned int time_diff = (unsigned int)(timer + milliseconds - current_time);
5062  timer = current_time + time_diff;
5063  cimg::sleep(time_diff);
5064  return time_diff;
5065  }

5090  // Use a custom RNG.
5091  inline unsigned int _rand(const unsigned int seed=0, const bool set_seed=false) {
5092  static cimg_ulong next = 0xB16B00B5;
5093  cimg::mutex(4);
5094  if (set_seed) next = (cimg_ulong)seed;
5095  next = next*1103515245 + 12345U;
5096  cimg::mutex(4,0);
5097  return (unsigned int)(next&0xFFFFFFU);
5098  }

5157  inline double grand() {
5158  double x1, w;
5159  do {
5160  const double x2 = cimg::rand(-1,1);
5161  x1 = cimg::rand(-1,1);
5162  w = x1*x1 + x2*x2;
5163  } while (w<=0 || w>=1.0);
5164  return x1*std::sqrt((-2*std::log(w))/w);
5165  }

5170  inline unsigned int prand(const double z) {
5171  if (z<=1.0e-10) return 0;
5172  if (z>100) return (unsigned int)((std::sqrt(z) * cimg::grand()) + z);
5173  unsigned int k = 0;
5174  const double y = std::exp(-z);
5175  for (double s = 1.0; s>=y; ++k) s*=cimg::rand();
5176  return k - 1;
5177  }

5389  template<typename T>
5390  inline T round(const T& x, const double y, const int rounding_type=0) {
5391  if (y<=0) return x;
5392  if (y==1) switch (rounding_type) {
5393  case 0 : return round(x);
5394  case 1 : return (T)std::ceil((_cimg_Tfloat)x);
5395  default : return (T)std::floor((_cimg_Tfloat)x);
5396  }
5397  const double sx = (double)x/y, floor = std::floor(sx), delta = sx - floor;
5398  return (T)(y*(rounding_type<0?floor:rounding_type>0?std::ceil(sx):delta<0.5?floor:std::ceil(sx)));
5399  }
5400 
5402  template<typename T>
5403  inline double cbrt(const T& x) {
5404 #if cimg_use_cpp11==1
5405  return std::cbrt(x);
5406 #else
5407  return x>=0?std::pow((double)x,1.0/3):-std::pow(-(double)x,1.0/3);
5408 #endif
5409  }

5413  template<typename T>
5414  inline T median(T val0, T val1) {
5415  return (val0 + val1)/2;
5416  }
